$CVS Larry Merlo is quite a wronged guy, I need to leave him with nice words... Everyone curses Larry because the stock was $115 in 2015 and $60 in 2020. Had he not made the painful decision to transform, CVS would be WBA price today. It takes time to integrate, and digest a $78B debt. Share price languished post merger from 2018 to 2020, despite growing profit and revenues consistently. I think Larry Merlo did a good job and all the dirty work, although a new CEO was needed to "change people's perception" on this perfectly good business.

Larry had the courage and vision to transform the business, all good leaders know painful decisions are required for long term relevance, this is far more important then even share price for the past 5 years. To me this is a responsible company to long term shareholders.
